The article discusses President Obama's visit to Mexico in April 2009 and the new approach to the bilateral relationship between the United States and Mexico. The focus of the visit was on addressing shared security challenges. One initiative mentioned is the Merida Initiative, a $1.4 billion package aimed at strengthening regional security cooperation with Mexico and other countries in the fight against drug and arms trafficking. The United States has committed $700 million to this initiative. The article also mentions efforts to combat arms trafficking and the sharing of information between the United States and Mexico. In addition to security, there is also a focus on clean energy and climate change. The United States and Mexico agree to launch a Bilateral Framework on Clean Energy and Climate Change, which will enhance cooperation and collaboration in these areas.